  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle and preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Rinse the&nbsp;<strong>freekeh</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold water</strong>, then&nbsp;add it to a pot, with a lid, with 500ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1L]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled&nbsp;water</strong> over a high heat&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 20-25 min or until cooked through, but with a slight bite</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> hazelnuts</strong> to a small baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 4-5 min or until they've slightly darkened</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Combine half of the <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>garlic</strong> (reserve the rest for step 6) with the<strong> Greek-style&nbsp;yoghurt</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and<span class=\"text-highlight\"> a pinch of</span>&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Mix well and set aside until serving</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Carefully add the <strong>eggs</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, cook for 7 min for perfect mid-boiled eggs</p>\r\n<p>Tip:&nbsp;the salt prevents the eggs from cracking</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>toasted</strong><strong> hazelnuts</strong> and<strong> cumin seeds</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong></p>\r\n<p>Blitz into a sandy nutty rubble (alternatively use a pestle and mortar)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Season generously with <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and stir in the <strong>nigella seeds</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; this is your <strong>dukkah</strong></p>\r\n<p>Transfer it to a plate and set aside&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Fill a bowl of <strong>cold water</strong> with ice (Gousto's ice packs are perfect)</p>\r\n<p>Once the<strong> eggs</strong>&nbsp;<span class=\"text-highlight\">are ready</span>, drain and add them to the ice water (to stop them cooking further)</p>\r\n<p>Tip: alternatively, run them under very cold water for 3 min, then set aside in a bowl of cold water</p>\r\n<p>Reserve the egg pot and give it a rinse out</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the<strong>&nbsp;cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>\r\n<p>Return the egg pot to a medium heat with 1-2 tsp <strong>olive oil</strong> (or a knob of <strong>butter</strong> for extra richness)</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> tomatoes</strong>, the remaining <strong>chopped&nbsp;garlic</strong>, <strong>harissa paste</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 5-7 min on until they've softened&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/450.step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
